Game day Badger Nation. The Badgers travel to Cherokee today for a 7:30 kickoff. Some guidelines for fans to follow this season. We will not have any victory lines on the field. In fact at no time before or after the game will fans be allowed on the field. There should be no physical contact with any of our players from fans before, during or after the games. Social distancing from other fans is encouraged. But, social distancing from the team is mandatory. No fans should be within 30 feet (10 yards) of the team at any time. We are very excited about the season starting and look forward to your support and encouragement of us this year.
https://www.uiltexas.org/files/policy/Pre-Game-Guidelines.pdf

post_text: Buckholts Lady Badgers Volleyball will take on Mt. Calm in Buckholts at 5:00 p.m. on Friday August. 14th. We have 8 players and each will be allowed 2 guests. We will place these guests on our list. Admission is $4 for adults and $2 for students. We will allow 12 additional fans at first come first serve, but no one will be allowed entry until 4:30. All fans must wear a mask to be granted entrance. We will allow seating on the first row, and the top row, but not the middle row. Fans must sit 6' apart, unless they are your immediate family. Please wash your hands before attending and hand sanitizer will be located by the door. No contact with players will be allowed, in fact fans are not allowed within 15' of the teams. Your co-operation, and understanding is appreciated, as well as your support. Thank you.

post_text:
Good afternoon Buckholts ISD families,

~ Remote Learning Meeting ~ Thursday, August 13, 2020 ~

We are excited to begin our school year next week. We understand that there are many unknowns that may lead to uncertainty and potential anxieties. At Buckholts ISD, we strive to keep our families and students informed as the current situation changes.

A representative of all students who are signed up to complete their education remotely should plan to join us for a meeting. Families may join us in the cafeteria or via Facebook Live on Thursday, August 13, 2020, at 6:30 pm for a required informational meeting.

The meeting will cover the required policies that are set forth by the Texas Education Agency (TEA), Buckholts ISD policies, and the procedures that Buckholts ISD will follow for remote learning students. We look forward to meeting with you and providing you with Buckholts ISD’s plan for remote learning.

Respectfully,

Buckholts ISD Administration

post_text:
A big Badger Welcome to our Superintendent Mr. Joe Oliver!! 🐾

My name is Joe Oliver. I have the privilege to serve as the Superintendent of the Buckholts Independent School District.
I have 42 years of experience as a professional educator. I have served as a teacher, coach, athletic director, assistant principal, principal, director of special programs, and as superintendent. In my opinion,
serving as an educator is a calling. I feel very Blessed to be a part of this community and the Buckholts ISD. Our door is always open and I encourage you to contact me with questions or concerns.

I have been very impressed with the students and staff of our district. I look forward to the start of the 20-21 school year.

With warmest regards,

Joe Oliver
Superintendent

The current hot topic is is P-EBT (Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer). This is also known as P-SNAP which is money on a benefit card to purchase food.

P-EBT is a one-time benefit for families that have lost access to free and reduced-price meals because of school closures related to COVID-19.

The link to receive this will not be open until June 1, 2020.

If you have questions please email chernandez@buckholtsisd.net

post_text:
Adopt a Senior! 🖤🧡

Hello my name is Ashlynne Kessler! I am 17 years old and I have attended Buckholts ISD for 6 years. I have been involved in Cross Country for about 3 years , I played Volleyball and Basketball for 4 years of high school , I ran track 3 years of high school. I have been in the National Honor Society for about 2 1/2 years I am also the secretary of NHS, I am the Vice President in FFA I have showed lambs for 2 years, I am the Student Council Secretary/ Treasurer and I am also my class Secretary/ Treasurer. After I graduate I plan on going to college and getting a degree in either Design or maybe even art. A few things that I enjoy are drawing, rearranging my room ALOT😂 , and finding new projects to do and being creative!

Adopt A Senior 🧡🖤
Julissaa Cardona
Hi, I’m Julissa Cardona and I’ve attended Buckholts ISD for 14 years. My years here at Buckholts ISD has been the best time of my life. I’ve really enjoyed the time I’ve spent here and it truly makes me sad that it’s all coming to an end. Although my senior year was cut short the first part of it was amazing. I made some life lasting moments and I am forever grateful for the people that have entered my life. I will miss practicing with my teammates and I hope my underclassmen know how much i love them and how much I’m going to miss them.

Busses will run at 10:30. If you need to make arrangements for your students please call the school at 254-593-2477.
